## ğŸ“ˆ Model Training

Model training is performed inside the Kaggle notebook:

```
notebooks/training_notebook.ipynb
```

This notebook includes:

* Data loading
* EDA
* Feature engineering
* Model training
* Evaluation
* Saving model

---

## ğŸ“Š Model Evaluation

We evaluate the models using:

* MAE (Mean Absolute Error)
* RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error)

Example output:

```json
{
  "LinearRegression": {
    "MAE": 185000,
    "RMSE": 245000
  },
  "RandomForest": {
    "MAE": 92000,
    "RMSE": 135000
  }
}
```

Saved in:

```
outputs/metrics.json
```

---

## ğŸ“Œ Feature Importance

Random Forest feature importance is visualized and saved as:

```
outputs/feature_importance.png
```

This helps understand which features affect house price most.

